not a toy, all right?

09:44.250 --> 09:48.311
But, Dad- But, Daddy-
Look, when you're older,
I'll teach you.

09:48.387 --> 09:50.412
All right?

09:50.489 --> 09:54.323
But Grandpa says I
should learn to shoot for protection.

09:54.393 --> 09:56.623
He says there's niggers
in the woods.

09:56.696 --> 09:59.859
<i>Cody, I want you</i>
<i>to apologize right now.</i>

10:00.933 --> 10:03.663
What?
I want him to tell Ada he's sorry.

10:03.736 --> 10:05.795
- Ada doesn't mind.
- I mind.

10:05.871 --> 10:08.431
- Clyde, what in tarnation's
gotten into you?
- Apologize.

10:08.507 --> 10:11.101
I-

10:11.177 --> 10:13.907
Apologize!
I'm sorry, Ada.

10:16.983 --> 10:18.917
Excuse me.

10:21.220 --> 10:23.450
Finished?
Uh, no.

10:24.657 --> 10:28.024
- I'm sorry about that, Ada.
- It ain't his fault.

10:28.094 --> 10:32.428
I know the boy doesn't mean it.
He just pick it up from his grandpa.

10:43.109 --> 10:45.669
<i>[ Sam Narrating ]</i>
<i>I spent the rest ofbreakfast</i>
<i>trying to explain to Lilly...</i>

10:45.745 --> 10:51.342
<i>that thinking all blacks were bad</i>
<i>was just as closed-minded</i>
<i>as thinking all whites were good.</i>

10:52.351 --> 10:56.412
<i>Her response made me realize</i>
<i>just how blind bigotry could be.</i>

10:56.489 --> 10:59.287
<i>All I could do was hope Al</i>
<i>could tell me what I was here for,</i>

10:59.358 --> 11:03.089
<i>so I could get it done and leap</i>
<i>to someplace I understood.</i>

11:03.162 --> 11:06.097
Hey, Clyde, you beat me here
this mornin'.

11:06.165 --> 11:11.068
That's a first. Especially considerin'
you was up all night last night.
[ Chuckling ]

11:11.137 --> 11:13.935
Yeah.
Excuse me.

11:17.109 --> 11:22.604
- Ain't you boys here a little early?
- It says right there the registration
office opens at 1 0:00.

11:22.682 --> 11:24.673
Office opens when we get here.

11:24.750 --> 11:27.344
Well, Mr. Thompson
would like to register to vote.

11:27.420 --> 11:32.323
Oh, uh, yeah, okay.
I'll get some papers out,
and we can get started.

11:32.391 --> 11:34.882
No, no, we don't need to do that.

11:34.960 --> 11:37.451
We can handle this right here.

11:37.530 --> 11:39.464
First, I got a couple
of questions for the boy.

11:39.532 --> 11:43.127
Mr. Thompson is 58 years old,

11:43.202 --> 11:46.262
and he's been an employee
of this county for over 30 years.

11:46.338 --> 11:49.774
- I'd appreciate it if you'd address him-
-" I'd appreciate it''?

11:49.842 --> 11:52.936
You watch your mouth.

11:53.012 --> 11:56.311
Now, who was the 1 9th president
of the United States?

11:56.382 --> 12:01.251
- Rutherford B. Hayes.
- What's the Eighth Amendment?

12:01.320 --> 12:05.381
Excessive bail
shall not be required,

12:05.458 --> 12:08.689
nor excessive fines imposed,

12:08.761 --> 12:12.925
nor cruel and unusual punishment
be inflicted.

12:22.975 --> 12:24.909
Read this.

12:30.549 --> 12:35.509
"We, the people of the United States,

12:35.588 --> 12:39.820
in order to form a more perfect union,

12:39.892 --> 12:42.019
establish justice,

12:42.094 --> 12:47.031
insure domestic
tranq-q-q- tranquillity''-

12:47.099 --> 12:51.433
You call that readin'?
Sounded like readin' to me.

12:51.504 --> 12:53.438
Well, I clocked him
at 1 2 words per minute.

12:53.506 --> 12:57.306
- Law says you gotta read at least
30 words per minute.
- What law?

12:58.978 --> 13:03.438
Look, he answered your questions,
and he read what you asked him to, so-

13:03.516 --> 13:06.314
You wait here a minute.

13:07.953 --> 13:10.387
What the hell is wrong with you?

13:10.456 --> 13:12.390
What do you mean?

13:14.827 --> 13:16.761
I thought this was all over
when you joined us last night,

13:16.829 --> 13:18.820
or have you forgot
about that oath you took?

13:18.898 --> 13:22.061
Look, the man has a right to vote.
He's a nigger.

13:22.134 --> 13:26.036
<i>[ Al ]</i>
<i>This isn't why you're here, Sam.</i>
What?

13:26.105 --> 13:29.040
I said, he's a nigger,
and if we don't stop them,

13:29.108 --> 13:31.303
they're gonna have us
all out of our jobs.

13:32.578 --> 13:34.637
- Then why am I here?
- It's Nathaniel-

13:34.713 --> 13:38.240
- Same reason I'm here.
- <i>Ada's son, the young man</i>
<i>standing behind me.</i>

13:39.451 --> 13:41.385
<i>They hang him, Sam.</i>

13:47.193 --> 13:49.127
Oh, boy.

13:51.430 --> 13:54.888
<i>White folks have gotta stick together,</i>
<i>or the niggers'll take over.</i>

13:54.967 --> 13:56.958
Hell, they're outbreedin' us now.

13:57.036 --> 13:59.504
Gene says in 30 years
we'll be a minority.

13:59.572 --> 14:02.405
<i>[ Al ]</i>
<i>Agree with him, Sam.</i>
No.

14:02.474 --> 14:04.601
Yes!

14:04.677 --> 14:06.736
I'm startin' to wonder
whether givin' you this job
was such a good idea.

14:06.812 --> 14:10.213
If you wanna save Nathaniel,
you gotta get this jerk
to think you're on his side.

14:10.282 --> 14:12.011
I can't.
You can't what?

14:12.084 --> 14:16.783
<i>Sam, it's like being behind enemy lines.</i>
<i>If you want to spy on the enemy,</i>
<i>you gotta act and talk like the enemy</i>-

14:16.856 --> 14:20.849
You can't what?
to get the info to save the good guys,
even if you have to do something hateful.

14:20.926 --> 14:25.124
I can't let those...

14:28.000 --> 14:29.968
niggers register.

14:30.035 --> 14:33.698
- Hey, what's a man have to do to get
a cup of coffee around here?
- Hey, Otis.

14:33.772 --> 14:37.105
Hi, Tom.
We were tryin' to register to vote.

14:37.176 --> 14:40.976
- You were bein' uppity with me.
- If questioning your testing methods...

14:41.046 --> 14:45.915
<i>is getting uppity, then maybe we should</i>
<i>have a look at the registration laws,</i>
<i>assuming you can read them.</i>

14:45.985 --> 14:49.716
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
Now,just hold your horses.

14:49.788 --> 14:51.722
Now, Tom, there oughta be
somethin' we could do.

14:53.359 --> 14:55.793
I'd love to, Sheriff.

14:55.861 --> 14:58.091
But he has to pass the literacy test.
Ain't that right, Clyde?

14:58.163 --> 15:00.290
Enemy lines, Sam.

15:03.235 --> 15:05.203
The law is the law.

15:05.271 --> 15:07.762
<i>Andjust what does</i>
<i>that law say, Clyde?</i>

15:11.043 --> 15:16.606
It says that, uh, you-
you boys have to go home...

15:16.682 --> 15:19.014
<i>and study a little bit harder,</i>

15:19.084 --> 15:21.746
<i>then you can come back</i>
<i>and-and-and try again.</i>

15:21.820 --> 15:25.950
Good.
But you only got two more chances
till, uh, next election.

15:26.025 --> 15:31.224
Clyde, why don't you, uh-
Why don't you show these
fine gentlemen to their car?

15:31.297 --> 15:34.198
It's a long ways, and I wouldn't
want 'em to get lost.

15:34.266 --> 15:37.702
I'll thank you, no.
We can find it ourselves.

15:37.770 --> 15:39.761
No, wait a second.

15:40.806 --> 15:43.240
No, you let me get you down there
to your car,

15:43.309 --> 15:48.178
'cause it is a long way,
and I'll just lead you down there, guys.

15:48.247 --> 15:51.148
It's right this way. Come on.
Come on. Right down here, huh?

15:51.216 --> 15:53.150
[ Chuckling ]
<i>Here we go.</i>

15:53.218 --> 15:56.449
<i>Right over here.</i>
<i>Let me get the door here for you.</i>

15:56.522 --> 16:00.185
<i>There you are.</i>
<i>Your chariot awaits you.</i>

16:00.259 --> 16:03.490
Look-
I thought you were the one
white man I could count on...

16:03.562 --> 16:05.393
but now you're callin' us
niggers and boys!

16:05.464 --> 16:07.989
I don't understand you!
I'm sorry.

16:08.067 --> 16:10.900
You set us up!
You made us look like fools!
I set you up?

16:10.970 --> 16:14.064
Oh, come on. I can't believe
you're gonna deny it now.

16:14.139 --> 16:16.073
Who else told us
to come down here?

16:16.141 --> 16:18.803
I don't know
if you did or you didn't.

16:18.877 --> 16:21.311
Maybe I did, but-
Maybe?

16:21.380 --> 16:24.440
And maybe you wrote me
all those letters in college...

16:24.516 --> 16:27.713
about all men being equal,
and it's time for a change, huh?

16:27.786 --> 16:29.720
Maybe you forgot about that too!

16:29.788 --> 16:33.554
Listen to me.
Everything I said up there
I did not mean, all right?

16:33.625 --> 16:37.356
What if I called you a rednecked,

16:37.429 --> 16:40.523
white-butted stump,
dumb cracker?

16:42.101 --> 16:47.368
That still stings, doesn't it,
even if I didn't mean it?

17:07.925 --> 17:10.019
I feel like I'm gonna throw up, Al.

17:11.630 --> 17:14.098
Yeah, I can understand it.

17:14.165 --> 17:16.726
I mean,
the guy I'm here to save probably,
and I completely tick him off.

17:16.801 --> 17:19.464
This is not working!
You just gotta hang in there.

17:19.538 --> 17:21.597
No, I don't have to
just hang in there!

17:21.673 --> 17:23.732
I-I-I can- I can do something else.

17:23.809 --> 17:26.039
I can solve this another way.
You can't do somethin' else.

17:26.111 --> 17:28.102
Ziggy doesn't even know
why he was hung.

17:28.180 --> 17:31.081
You're just gonna have to act
like you're in the Klan
and see this thing through.

17:31.150 --> 17:33.277
Ziggy doesn't even know
why he was killed.

17:33.352 --> 17:35.445
Well, there's no data
on that kind of stuff.

17:35.521 --> 17:38.649
Nobody prints it in the newspapers.
Nobody puts it on the county records.

17:38.724 --> 17:41.921
It just happens,
and it gets buried.

17:41.994 --> 17:44.554
But I'll bet it had somethin' to do
with voter registration.

17:44.630 --> 17:47.724
I gotta talk to Nathaniel.
He's not gonna listen to you now.

17:47.800 --> 17:50.200
No, he's not gonna listen to me,
because you told me I had to act...

17:50.269 --> 17:52.294
like I was on the side
of that jerk Tom!

17:52.371 --> 17:54.771
Well, that's because
if you didn't do that,

17:54.840 --> 17:58.105
you wouldn't find out
how or when Nathaniel gets hanged.

17:58.177 --> 18:00.839
- Now,just chill out!
- <i>Chill out?</i>

18:00.913 --> 18:03.313
<i>I'm the one in the K.K.K.,</i>
<i>not you. You're not</i>-

18:06.251 --> 18:09.152
<i>I know you're gonna hate it,</i>
<i>but go on up into that courthouse...</i>

18:09.221 --> 18:11.781
and find out what's on
those worms' minds.

18:11.857 --> 18:16.385
Worms, yeah. Worms.
I never could stand worms,
even if I was usin' them for bait.

18:16.462 --> 18:18.930
<i>Hey, Clyde,you all right?</i>

18:18.997 --> 18:21.363
Uh, yeah. Yeah, I'm okay.

18:21.433 --> 18:24.459
I, uh, was just, uh-

18:26.038 --> 18:28.063
just yellin' at some-

18:29.475 --> 18:32.035
some nigger kids to stay
away from your car.

18:32.111 --> 18:34.341
Well, I appreciate that.

18:44.690 --> 18:49.150
<i>[ Sam Narrating ]</i>
<i>I spent the afternoon finding fault</i>
<i>with every black applicant that came in...</i>

18:49.228 --> 18:52.322
<i>and felt smaller and smaller</i>
<i>with each one I sent away.</i>
<i>* [ Gospel ]</i>

18:53.332 --> 18:57.530
<i>But the real horror of the day</i>
<i>was when I ended up alone with Tom</i>-
<i>* [ Children Singing ]</i>

18:57.603 --> 19:01.903
<i>and found myself sitting through</i>
<i>one sick black joke after another.</i>

19:01.974 --> 19:06.673
<i>I hated it.</i>
<i>* [ Children Sing Off-Key ]</i>

19:06.745 --> 19:09.714
Boy, well,
they almost got that one.
[ Chuckling ]

19:09.781 --> 19:14.650
I think the good Lord loves
the off-key ones the most,
'cause he sure helps them to sing the loudest.

19:14.720 --> 19:17.154
Ain't that the truth.
[ Chuckles ]

19:17.222 --> 19:20.555
If I don't hurry up and get this done,
I'm gonna be late
for choir practice myself.

19:20.626 --> 19:24.084
Here, you want some help, Ada?
You like stringin' beans, Mr. Clyde?

19:24.163 --> 19:27.223
No. No, not really, but, uh,

19:27.299 --> 19:30.029
I don't imagine you care for it
much yourself, huh?

19:30.102 --> 19:32.093
Amen to that.

19:36.775 --> 19:39.141
Ada?
Mmm?

19:39.211 --> 19:41.202
I want to talk to you about
what happened this morning.

19:42.314 --> 19:44.680
Didn't nothin' happen this mornin'.
Yes, it did.

19:46.518 --> 19:48.509
I'm talkin' about
what Cody said.

19:50.289 --> 19:52.280
I'm sorry about that.
It was wrong and-

19:53.358 --> 19:56.293
It's not about wrong
or right, Mr. Clyde.

19:56.361 --> 20:01.230
It's just the way things is.
Well, I don't believe that.

20:02.868 --> 20:05.530
I know you don't, Mr. Clyde.
You never did.

20:05.604 --> 20:08.767
But yours is just one voice
speakin' in a hurricane.

20:10.275 --> 20:14.143
Yeah, well,
sometimes one voice is all you need.

20:14.213 --> 20:16.647
[ Chuckles ]
That's what my Nathaniel says.

20:16.715 --> 20:19.206
<i>* [ Continues ]</i>

20:19.284 --> 20:22.185
Your Nathaniel's
a very bright young man.
Mmm.

20:22.254 --> 20:24.882
And he's gonna make
a difference... someday.

20:24.957 --> 20:29.985
But right now,
he's gotta be very careful.

20:31.129 --> 20:35.259
You can't make spirits
like Nathaniel's be careful, Mr. Clyde.

20:35.334 --> 20:39.634
The Lord gives them the fire
to want to change things.

20:39.705 --> 20:43.801
Do you know he talked me into
goin' down to register tomorrow?

20:43.875 --> 20:49.575
That is, if I can pass the test.
Ada, I'll help you pass the test.

20:49.648 --> 20:51.843
Okay? But you've
gotta help me stop Nathaniel.

20:53.051 --> 20:56.077
From what?
Helpin' colored folks learn?

20:56.154 --> 20:59.453
No. No, from tryin' to take on
the whole town...

20:59.524 --> 21:01.754
when things don't happen
as fast as he wants them to.

21:01.827 --> 21:04.523
I can't change him, Mr. Clyde.

21:04.596 --> 21:09.056
Once that boy makes up his mind,
there ain't no talkin' about it,

21:09.134 --> 21:12.831
not from you and not from me.

21:18.977 --> 21:20.968
Boo!
Goodness!

21:21.046 --> 21:23.708
I'm a ghost, I'm a ghost,
I'm a ghost, I'm a ghost, I'm a ghost!
Cody, Cody, Cody, take this off.

21:23.782 --> 21:25.773
Take it off right now.
Take this off.

21:25.851 --> 21:27.842
Ada-

21:30.022 --> 21:31.990
What are you doin' with this?
I was just playin'.

21:32.057 --> 21:34.321
Well, this isn't somethin'
that you play with, son.

21:34.393 --> 21:37.226
But Bill's daddy has one,
and he lets him wear it.

21:37.296 --> 21:40.356
I don't care
what Bill's daddy does.

21:40.432 --> 21:42.866
But you're in the huntin' club
with him.

21:44.836 --> 21:48.169
It's not a huntin' club, son.
Then what kind of club is it?

21:48.240 --> 21:51.368
You know, for a little kid,
you ask a lot of big questions.

21:52.944 --> 21:55.208
I'll tell you what.

21:55.280 --> 21:58.044
Let me go inside
and get changed, all right?
Okay.

21:58.116 --> 22:00.050
Hang on here now,

22:00.118 --> 22:02.814
so your mom doesn't tan my hide
gettin' anything dirty.

22:02.888 --> 22:05.152
Thank you very much.
Then we'll go outside,

22:05.223 --> 22:07.157
I'll teach you how
to shoot this gun the right way,

22:07.225 --> 22:10.683
and maybe we'll talk about
the huntin' club a little bit, okay?
Okay.

22:10.762 --> 22:13.492
<i>[ Weapon Clicks ]</i>
<i>[ Sam ]</i>
<i>All right now. Watch those cans up there.</i>

22:13.565 --> 22:15.624
You watchin' 'em?

22:16.768 --> 22:18.759
Here we go.

22:25.777 --> 22:30.612
We're probably too far away
for this short of a barrel, you know?

22:31.883 --> 22:33.874
Let's move up here.

22:36.688 --> 22:39.350
Look, son, you know what it means
to be in the Klan?

22:39.424 --> 22:42.587
It means we're gonna stop
the coloreds from taking over.

22:43.695 --> 22:46.892
Taking over what?
I don't know.

22:48.567 --> 22:51.695
- You like Ada, don't you?
- Yeah, she's nice.

22:54.539 --> 22:58.600
Would you ever hurt her?
No. Why would I want to hurt Ada?

22:58.677 --> 23:01.646
<i>[ Sam ]</i>
<i>Maybe because her skin's</i>
<i>a different color.</i>

23:02.647 --> 23:05.741
<i>Some people are afraid</i>
<i>of things that are different.</i>

23:07.018 --> 23:09.987
<i>It's notjust skin color.</i>
<i>It could be religion or</i>-

23:10.055 --> 23:12.649
But then why didn't God
just make everybody the same?

23:12.724 --> 23:17.093
- Then it wouldn't matter.
- <i>Yeah, see, now,</i>
<i>that's exactly the point, Cody.</i>

23:17.162 --> 23:19.460
It doesn't matter
unless we make it matter.

23:19.531 --> 23:24.992
But Grandpa says it matters.
His papa told him,
and his papa before him told him,

23:25.070 --> 23:28.767
and nobody thought to say " stop.''

23:30.409 --> 23:33.310
See, it's up to you and me to say,

23:33.378 --> 23:35.437
"Stop. This is wrong.''

23:39.818 --> 23:43.845
Now, what do you say?
Let's see if you can hit that can.

23:43.922 --> 23:47.358
All right?
Tuck your shoulder in there.

23:47.426 --> 23:50.657
All right. Aim it up real good.
I'm gonna put the safety off.

23:50.729 --> 23:52.663
Got it aimed.
Now just squeeze that trigger.

23:55.367 --> 23:57.528
I hit it! Daddy, I hit it!

23:57.602 --> 23:59.763
Yes, you did. Yes, you did.

23:59.838 --> 24:01.772
This must be a kid's gun,
I guess, huh?

24:01.840 --> 24:04.604
Cody, why don't you
come on in now?

24:07.179 --> 24:09.374
Give me a kiss. Give me a kiss.

24:09.448 --> 24:11.439
Wash up for supper.

24:14.186 --> 24:18.145
I thought this was over.
Every generation has to learn it anew.

24:19.524 --> 24:22.322
Please, Clyde, I don't want you fillin'
his head with things that ain't true.

24:22.394 --> 24:26.125
- But it is true, and you know it.
- <i>Clyde.! Oh, Clyde.!</i>

24:26.198 --> 24:28.723
Come get your robe!
We got some work to do.

24:28.800 --> 24:31.462
- What's goin' on, Daddy?
- This is when they grab Nathaniel.

24:31.536 --> 24:33.970
- What are you talkin' about?
- I'm talkin' about club business.

24:34.039 --> 24:35.973
That's what I'm talkin' about.
Now, let's go.

24:36.041 --> 24:39.704
Nathaniel leads a march right
through the center of town tonight,

24:39.778 --> 24:43.976
and Grand Dragon-breath there
and his boys are gonna be
waitin' for him with guns and bats.

24:44.049 --> 24:48.145
- <i>This is where they hang him.</i>
- If this is about Nathaniel,
maybe I could go talk to him.

24:48.220 --> 24:50.211
We don't have no time to talk.

24:51.890 --> 24:53.824
<i>[ Door Closes ]</i>

24:53.892 --> 24:57.157
You don't have any choice, Sam.
It's the only way to save Nathaniel.

25:32.931 --> 25:36.264
<i>[ Sam Narrating ]</i>
<i>Terror, like the night,</i>
<i>knows no boundaries.</i>

25:36.334 --> 25:38.325
<i>By the time we had our robes on,</i>
<i>it was dark.</i>

25:38.403 --> 25:42.396
<i>And instead ofbeing taken</i>
<i>to a confrontation with Nathaniel,</i>

25:42.474 --> 25:45.932
<i>I found myself running towards</i>
<i>some new conflict</i>-

25:46.011 --> 25:49.879
<i>one that I feared</i>
<i>could only end in disaster.</i>

25:59.157 --> 26:01.091
[ Men ]
Surprise!

26:01.159 --> 26:04.151
[ Men Whooping ]

26:08.600 --> 26:13.037
What's goin' on?
You remember little old snipe hunts,
don't ya, Clyde?

26:13.104 --> 26:15.698
Oh.
[ Laughing ]

26:15.774 --> 26:21.110
- Looks like a practical joke, Sam.
What a bunch of simps.
- Yeah, well, uh,

26:21.179 --> 26:25.843
I thought we were gonna be,
you know, d-doin' somethin'.

26:25.917 --> 26:30.854
Oh, Brother Clyde, we got to
give ourselves some excuse
to get away from the womenfolk.

26:30.922 --> 26:34.414
That's right. And Klan business
is the best excuse I know.

26:34.492 --> 26:38.952
Except we got a good one anyway-
your one-day anniversary as a Klansman.

26:39.030 --> 26:43.399
Come on. Let's hear it!
[ Men Whooping ]

26:43.468 --> 26:46.699
Drinks on me!
Come on, guys!

26:47.706 --> 26:49.970
Excuse me, boys.
Clear the way, boys.

26:50.041 --> 26:53.169
<i>I got another surprise</i>
<i>for you, Clyde. Huh?</i>

26:53.244 --> 26:56.236
Oh, no, thanks.
I'm really not hungry.

26:56.314 --> 26:59.408
Well, now, Dot made this
special just for you.

26:59.484 --> 27:04.512
Don't go makin' me a liar,
'cause I know she's gonna be askin' me
how much you liked it.

27:04.589 --> 27:07.752
Yeah, okay. Thanks.
Thanks. Excuse me.

27:11.429 --> 27:16.093
Ziggy says that Nathaniel
still disappears tonight.

27:16.167 --> 27:18.795
It's okay.
It's okay?

27:18.870 --> 27:22.135
It's not " okay'' okay,
but this'll give me an opportunity
to find out what happens.

27:22.207 --> 27:24.334
That way I'll have an edge.

27:24.409 --> 27:26.377
Oh, so you can head 'em off at the pass.
Exactly.

27:26.444 --> 27:29.413
Gentlemen, brothers.

27:29.481 --> 27:32.917
Brother Tom has just given me
some very disparaging news.

27:33.918 --> 27:36.751
Nathaniel Simpson
and some of his nigger friends...

27:36.821 --> 27:39.813
are gonna demonstrate tonight,
violently, in town...

27:39.891 --> 27:43.327
<i>because of unfair voter registration.</i>

27:43.395 --> 27:47.354
- Are we gonna stand for this,
gentlemen?
- [ All ] No!

27:47.432 --> 27:51.596
Are we gonna let these people
defile our great, white city?

27:51.670 --> 27:56.039
- [ All ] No!
- Gentlemen, let's exercise
our duty as Klansmen.

27:56.107 --> 27:58.098
Let's go to town!
[ Men ]
Yeah!

27:59.678 --> 28:02.613
I need to borrow your car.
You can ride with me.

28:02.681 --> 28:05.707
No, no, see, I gotta- I gotta
go home and get my gun.

28:05.784 --> 28:07.877
Good. Good.
I'll meet you at the courthouse.
All right.

28:07.952 --> 28:11.911
That's good thinking, Sam.
I'll meet you at the church.

28:11.990 --> 28:14.117
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>Come on, boys.</i>
[ Men Chattering ]

28:14.192 --> 28:17.628
<i>Martin Luther King says</i>
<i>injustice anywhere...</i>

28:17.696 --> 28:20.790
is a threat to justice everywhere.
[ Men Shouting In Agreement ]

28:20.865 --> 28:25.529
<i>And so I'm askin'you now:</i>
<i>Don't forget our sacrifices</i>
<i>on Bloody Sunday.</i>

28:25.603 --> 28:29.801
Let us follow the brave footsteps
of those who marched
from Selma to Montgomery.

28:29.874 --> 28:31.808
Yeah!
[ Chattering In Agreement ]

28:31.876 --> 28:33.434
<i>[ Car Approaching ]</i>

28:38.550 --> 28:40.848
<i>Hey, Clyde.</i>
<i>What are you doin'here, Clyde?</i>

28:40.919 --> 28:44.116
<i>[ Men Chattering ]</i>

28:45.323 --> 28:50.886
- You can't march.
- We are entitled to express
our opinions in a public forum.

28:50.962 --> 28:54.159
That right is guaranteed
by the First Amendment.

28:54.232 --> 28:56.462
This is not about
the First Amendment.
<i>That's right.</i>

28:57.736 --> 29:01.001
This is about angry, frightened men
who want to make an example out of you.

29:02.373 --> 29:05.365
- Get him out of here.
- <i>[ Man ] What's he talkin'about?</i>

29:05.443 --> 29:08.640
- They're waiting for you at the courthouse.
- How do you know that?

29:08.713 --> 29:11.477
- 'Cause he's in the Klan. That's how.
- That's right. I am.

29:11.549 --> 29:13.983
We're not afraid of you!
<i>Well,you should be.</i>

29:14.052 --> 29:18.682
We outnumber you three-to-one.
We got guns, and God knows what else.

29:20.592 --> 29:23.755
We're gonna tell the townspeople
that we're not afraid of them-

29:23.828 --> 29:26.490
that we won't stand for injustice.

29:26.564 --> 29:29.032
This isn't working, Sam.
He still gets hanged.

29:29.100 --> 29:33.434
I'm askin' you... to trust me.

29:33.505 --> 29:36.804
- I did, remember?
- I was wrong.

29:38.009 --> 29:40.375
You come back tomorrow,
I'll make all that right.

29:40.445 --> 29:42.709
Oh, like you did this morning?
No, thank you.

29:42.781 --> 29:45.614
You're just tryin' to set us up again
like you did at the courthouse!

29:45.683 --> 29:47.878
<i>[ Men ]</i>
<i>Yeah.!</i>
No, I'm not trying to set you up.

29:47.952 --> 29:50.045
I just don't want to see
anybody get killed.

29:50.121 --> 29:52.715
It'll be a peaceful march.
<i>No, it won't.</i>

29:54.125 --> 29:57.720
- The Klan's not gonna let it be.
- Well, maybe we got
a few surprises for them!

29:57.796 --> 30:01.323
- Let's go!
- No, if you're gonna go,

30:01.399 --> 30:03.390
you gotta go through me.

30:03.468 --> 30:07.268
<i>[ Murmuring, Chattering ]</i>

30:07.338 --> 30:10.034
You can't take us all on,
Mr. Clyde.

30:12.811 --> 30:14.403
<i>[ Men Shouting ]</i>

30:14.479 --> 30:16.913
<i>[ Nathaniel ]</i>
<i>No, stop.! Everybody, stop.!</i>

30:16.981 --> 30:19.313
Maybe it's time we hung one of them!
[ Men ]
Yeah!

30:19.384 --> 30:22.547
No. No. Let him go.

30:28.159 --> 30:31.287
All right. The march is off.
What?

30:31.362 --> 30:35.423
Listen. Now,
if he's tellin' the truth,

30:35.500 --> 30:38.196
then we won't accomplish
what we set out for.

30:38.269 --> 30:40.237
That's it, Sam. That's it.
You changed history.

30:40.305 --> 30:43.433
<i>The attack doesn't happen.</i>
Thank God.

30:43.508 --> 30:47.205
- What'd you say?
- I said, thank God.

30:47.278 --> 30:50.372
Now- Now nobody's gonna get hurt.

30:50.448 --> 30:54.748
Well, Mr. Clyde,
we might not march tonight,
but we will march.

30:54.819 --> 30:57.413
- I know that.
- And we will win.

30:57.488 --> 31:00.787
I know that too.

31:06.865 --> 31:09.060
Great job, Sam.
<i>[ Banging ]</i>

31:21.012 --> 31:22.946
<i>Hey.</i>
Hey.

31:23.014 --> 31:27.280
- Back so soon?
- What?

31:27.352 --> 31:32.551
- How was your party?
- Oh, uh, it was fine.

31:32.624 --> 31:34.615
<i>How'd you know about it?</i>

31:34.692 --> 31:37.855
It wasn't exactly the biggest secret
in the whole wide world.

31:39.964 --> 31:42.432
It's just that we...

31:43.668 --> 31:48.628
womenfolk like to let our big,
strong men think that it was.

31:50.074 --> 31:52.065
Cody's asleep.

31:55.546 --> 31:57.480
Yeah, yeah.

31:59.817 --> 32:03.947
Listen, Lilly, uh,
how do you feel about Ada?

32:05.590 --> 32:09.959
Please, Clyde, I don't want to argue
about the Klan right now.

32:10.028 --> 32:11.962
I really think we need
to talk about this.

32:12.030 --> 32:14.999
Why are you so concerned
about the coloreds anyway?

32:15.066 --> 32:17.000
Why aren't you more concerned
about us?

32:17.068 --> 32:19.628
The coloreds,
they got that N.A.A.C.P.

32:19.704 --> 32:21.865
Us whites are out here
all by ourselves.

32:21.940 --> 32:23.931
The Klan is the only thing
we got fightin' for us.

32:24.008 --> 32:26.533
What are you so afraid of?

32:26.611 --> 32:30.069
I don't want coloreds
sittin' in my restaurants.

32:30.148 --> 32:33.083
I don't want 'em livin' next door
and destroyin' the neighborhood,

32:33.151 --> 32:37.315
marryin' whites,
takin' our jobs.

32:37.388 --> 32:39.481
Listen to me, Lilly.

32:40.491 --> 32:42.425
They're people.

32:42.493 --> 32:44.893
They're just like you and me.

32:44.963 --> 32:48.262
And all they want
is to be treated like we are.

32:48.333 --> 32:51.029
Now, they shouldn't have to die
to get that.
<i>[ Weapon Cocks ]</i>

32:52.570 --> 32:56.199
Mighty strange you didn't
show up at the courthouse.

32:56.274 --> 32:58.868
Neither did your march-happy
coon friends.

32:58.943 --> 33:02.674
I guess that means you told 'em.
Tell them that's not true,
Clyde. Tell them.

33:04.649 --> 33:06.583
Tell them it's not true.

33:06.651 --> 33:10.417
I couldn't stand by and let
innocent people be murdered.

33:10.488 --> 33:13.252
You defied the Holy Order
of the Brotherhood.

33:13.324 --> 33:16.691
Daddy, he was just worried
that somebody was gonna get hurt.
That's all.

33:16.761 --> 33:18.922
He's a spy for the niggers or the feds.

33:18.997 --> 33:22.364
Will you say somethin'?
Tell them it's not true!

33:22.433 --> 33:25.561
The only reason he joined us,
Lilly, was to take us down.

33:25.636 --> 33:29.128
I had to try and stop
one night of violence.

33:29.207 --> 33:33.007
<i>Well,you did it, so now we</i>
<i>gotta do somethin'drastic.</i>

33:33.077 --> 33:35.011
We gotta do somethin'
so that your colored friends...

33:35.079 --> 33:37.377
will understand
that this is a white man's world.

33:38.683 --> 33:40.913
<i>[ Portal Opens ]</i>

33:40.985 --> 33:43.954
Daddy, what are you gonna do?
They've decided to blow up the church.

33:44.022 --> 33:47.014
<i>I'm gonna do what Brother Tom said</i>-
There were 1 5 little kids in there...

33:47.091 --> 33:50.720
and two adults, including Ada-
all killed.

34:05.376 --> 34:07.071
<i>* [ Gospel ]</i>

34:07.145 --> 34:11.206
<i>* [ Woman Singing ]</i>

34:11.282 --> 34:14.274
<i>* [ Choir Singing ]</i>

34:24.996 --> 34:27.987
[ Chattering ]

34:30.333 --> 34:34.498
You know,
you're worse than a nigger.
You're a white nigger.

34:34.572 --> 34:37.438
<i>[ Chattering Continues ]</i>

34:37.507 --> 34:39.498
And the penalty for that
is death.

34:39.577 --> 34:43.911
So the truth is, you don't care
who you kill- black or white.

34:43.981 --> 34:46.245
- Hey, boy!
- Grady!

34:57.195 --> 35:00.494
Son, I- I just
don't understand you.

35:00.565 --> 35:03.090
You know how I've always
liked you and respected you.

35:03.167 --> 35:06.659
Maybe sometimes
I didn't show it.

35:06.737 --> 35:10.764
My daughter and my grandson,
they love you a great deal.

35:10.842 --> 35:14.039
Damn it, I just tried to show you...

35:14.112 --> 35:18.845
what I was doin' to protect my part
of the world and my family!

35:18.916 --> 35:20.850
That's all I did.

35:23.855 --> 35:26.346
If you love your family,
don't do this to them.

35:26.424 --> 35:28.358
I'm not doing it to them.

35:30.128 --> 35:34.326
You bomb the church,
they'll put you away for that.

35:34.398 --> 35:39.062
And if you kill me, who's gonna take care
of your daughter, raise your grandson?

35:39.137 --> 35:42.004
I'm not gonna kill you.

35:43.040 --> 35:45.133
You don't know me at all,
do you?

35:46.477 --> 35:49.002
I don't know any man
who'd dynamite a church.

35:49.080 --> 35:51.480
I'm not just any man.

35:58.956 --> 36:01.823
- <i>[ Portal Opens ]</i>
- Sam, you gotta get outta here!

36:01.893 --> 36:04.589
<i>Come on.! Get up.! That church</i>
<i>is gonna blow in seven minutes.!</i>

36:04.662 --> 36:07.358
- I'm tryin', Al.
- Well, you gotta try harder.

36:07.431 --> 36:09.558
We gotta find somethin'
to untie you.

36:09.634 --> 36:11.795
We gotta find somethin'
to untie you. Uh, here.

36:11.869 --> 36:15.327
Come on over here and knock
this sign off the wall
and break the glass.

36:15.406 --> 36:18.239
<i>Maybe you can cut the ropes.</i>
<i>Hurry up.!</i>

36:18.309 --> 36:20.300
Seven minutes.

36:22.480 --> 36:25.244
Come on! Knock it off the wall, Sam!
Don't look at it!

36:25.316 --> 36:29.218
[ Grunting ]
Come on!
We haven't got any time!

36:29.287 --> 36:31.221
Al. Al.
What?

36:31.289 --> 36:33.416
Go over to the church.
"Go over to the church''?
What can I do?

36:33.491 --> 36:36.927
I'm a hologram!
They're children, Al.
Little children.

36:36.994 --> 36:39.690
That's right!
That's right, that's right!
They're kids!

36:39.764 --> 36:42.961
God bless the children!
All right. Uh, cut the rope!

36:44.135 --> 36:47.127
[ Grunting ]

36:53.945 --> 36:55.412
<i>[ Glass Breaking ]</i>

36:55.479 --> 36:57.913
<i>* [ Continues ]</i>

37:12.797 --> 37:15.288
<i>[ Al ] Everybody stop singin',</i>
<i>stop singin', stop singin'.!</i>
<i>You gotta be quiet.!</i>

37:15.366 --> 37:18.096
<i>[ Children Gasping, Shouting,</i>
<i>Squealing ]</i>

37:18.169 --> 37:20.899
- For heaven sakes, children,
what is the matter?
- There's a ghost!

37:20.972 --> 37:23.406
<i>It's not a ghost.</i>
<i>It's an angel.</i>

37:23.474 --> 37:25.408
No way.
Not with those clothes.

37:26.611 --> 37:29.273
Who are you talking to, child?
Listen.
I'm here to try and help you.

37:29.347 --> 37:31.577
- It's the Lord.
- What?

37:31.649 --> 37:34.174
- No, I'm not the Lord.
- It's Abraham Lincoln.

37:34.252 --> 37:38.484
<i>No, it's not. He has a beard.</i>
<i>That's some crazy white man.</i>

37:54.438 --> 37:56.372
<i>[ Door Opens ]</i>

37:57.675 --> 37:59.040
Cody?

38:00.611 --> 38:03.842
Listen, I may be crazy,
but you've gotta tell the big ones...

38:03.914 --> 38:05.848
that you've gotta get
out of the church!

38:05.916 --> 38:08.350
Get out! Get out!
[ Shouting, Screaming ]

38:08.419 --> 38:10.887
Children, children, children,
come back here!

38:10.955 --> 38:14.618
Lord, save my soul. Will somebody
please tell me what is happening here?

38:14.692 --> 38:17.320
There's gonna be a big boom here!
Get the kids out!

38:17.395 --> 38:20.125
[ Screaming, Shouting Continue ]

38:27.705 --> 38:29.696
Stay in the car!

38:34.245 --> 38:36.008
Daddy!

38:39.083 --> 38:41.142
<i>[ Lilly ]</i>
<i>Clyde.!</i>

38:41.218 --> 38:45.086
God! I tried to stop 'em!
I swear I tried!

38:45.156 --> 38:47.920
[ Chattering ]
<i>[ Cody ]</i>
<i>Daddy.!</i>

38:49.060 --> 38:51.221
<i>[ Chattering Continues ]</i>

38:51.295 --> 38:54.822
Al? Al!

38:54.899 --> 38:56.890
<i>[ Lilly ]</i>
<i>No, Clyde, don't.!</i>

38:58.636 --> 39:00.831
Sam, I got all the children out.
They're safe.

39:00.905 --> 39:03.601
- Oh, thank God.
- Come on. Come on, kids.

39:03.674 --> 39:07.610
That's it, that's it.
Little ones with the big ones.
Come on.

39:16.320 --> 39:19.346
- You bastards!
- No, Nathaniel, no!

39:19.423 --> 39:22.051
[ Men Shouting ]

39:22.126 --> 39:24.287
Get him over there by the tree!
Let's string him up!

39:24.362 --> 39:27.422
You hold him here. You stay here.
Daddy! Daddy!

39:27.498 --> 39:30.524
- Please take care of the children.
- Get up here, boy.

39:32.269 --> 39:36.365
You like this heat? Well,
that's just a taste of where you're goin'.

39:41.145 --> 39:44.774
Friends, I stand before you
in the name of justice...

39:44.849 --> 39:47.545
and of the holy white race.

39:47.618 --> 39:51.554
This man has tried
to destroy our way of life,

39:51.622 --> 39:55.524
<i>[ Men ] Yeah.</i>
<i>and now he must pay</i>
<i>the ultimate penalty.</i>

39:56.560 --> 39:58.528
<i>I agree with the Grand Dragon.</i>

39:58.596 --> 40:01.963
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>What? What's he doin'?</i>
<i>[ Murmuring ]</i>

40:03.300 --> 40:07.964
I agree with
the Grand Dragon 1 00%.

40:08.038 --> 40:10.905
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>What?</i>
<i>[ Murmuring ]</i>

40:16.781 --> 40:19.011
I think we should hang this man.
Tie this off.

40:19.083 --> 40:21.984
<i>[ Murmuring ]</i>

40:22.052 --> 40:27.183
And while we're at it,
I think you should hang me too.

40:27.258 --> 40:32.161
- Sam, have you gone completely crazy?
- Daddy! No, Daddy! You gotta stop this!

40:32.229 --> 40:35.756
<i>Because I don't want to live in a world</i>
<i>where fear and hate...</i>

40:36.867 --> 40:38.994
hide behind a call for justice.

40:41.605 --> 40:45.166
<i>Where men, women and children,</i>

40:46.877 --> 40:49.004
born as free as you and me,

40:50.114 --> 40:53.049
are denied, among other things,
the right to vote.

40:54.051 --> 40:56.144
And if they try
to do anything about it,

40:57.254 --> 40:59.449
<i>you hang 'em...</i>

41:00.791 --> 41:02.782
<i>or you blow 'em up in a church.</i>

41:02.860 --> 41:07.661
<i>They're so proud of what they're doin',</i>
<i>these dispensers ofjustice,</i>

41:08.866 --> 41:10.993
that they have to hide
behind masks to do it.

41:11.068 --> 41:12.797
[ Chattering ]

41:15.072 --> 41:18.098
Cody.

41:18.175 --> 41:20.405
Cody, you look at me, son.

41:22.847 --> 41:24.906
This is not justice.

41:27.585 --> 41:30.019
This is merely a desperate attempt...

41:30.087 --> 41:33.488
to hang on to the past-
a shameful past...

41:33.557 --> 41:38.051
that can never and should never
be restored.

41:38.128 --> 41:40.221
<i>[ Murmuring ]</i>

41:40.297 --> 41:45.496
So go ahead.
You hang us now.

41:47.838 --> 41:49.829
<i>But you cannot stop the future,</i>

41:51.575 --> 41:54.442
because you cannot kill everyone
who was here tonight,

41:55.546 --> 41:57.673
and they will never forget
what they saw.

41:59.917 --> 42:02.215
Hell, I say if he wants to hang,
let's get it over with!

42:02.286 --> 42:04.516
- <i>Clyde, no.!</i>
- [ Shouting ]

42:04.588 --> 42:07.455
<i>Grady, start her up.!</i>

42:07.525 --> 42:09.390
[ Engine Starts ]

42:09.460 --> 42:11.451
<i>Put her in gear.</i>

42:19.270 --> 42:21.568
Ready!

42:21.639 --> 42:24.437
Take 'em down.
What?

42:24.508 --> 42:29.207
You heard me.
He betrayed us.
He deserves to die.

42:29.280 --> 42:32.044
Take him down and Nathaniel too.

42:32.116 --> 42:35.711
<i>Listen, old man,</i>
<i>if you ain't got what it takes,</i>

42:35.786 --> 42:39.313
maybe there's another man here
better to get the job done.

42:39.390 --> 42:41.551
I lost one son.

42:41.625 --> 42:43.752
I don't intend to lose another.

42:44.695 --> 42:46.890
[ Gasps ]
Oh, my God.

42:54.738 --> 42:57.002
[ Grunting ]

43:13.557 --> 43:15.991
<i>[ Murmuring ]</i>

43:22.166 --> 43:24.100
I'm okay, Mama.

43:24.168 --> 43:26.796
Sam, that was unbelievable.
I don't believe it. You did it!

43:26.870 --> 43:29.361
I'm so proud of you.
I love you so much.

43:29.440 --> 43:33.103
I'm so glad you're here.
I am too.

43:33.177 --> 43:37.477
Oh, Sam, uh, on August 3,
Lyndon Johnson passes
the Voting Rights Act,

43:37.548 --> 43:41.814
and Nathaniel becomes one of
the first black mayors of Alabama.

43:57.001 --> 43:59.834
<i>Hey, Frank.! I swept the floor</i>
<i>and took out the trash.</i>

43:59.903 --> 44:02.463
<i>Uh, can I go to Phil's</i>
<i>for some candy?</i>

44:02.539 --> 44:05.372
- Sure.
- Really?

44:05.442 --> 44:07.637
You haven't rinsed her yet!

44:07.711 --> 44:10.145
- <i>Is that</i>- <i>Is that to0-</i>
- Frank, it's too hot.

44:10.214 --> 44:12.546
Yeah. Um-
<i>[ Phone Ringing ]</i>

44:12.616 --> 44:17.576
Where's Kyle?
He went to,
uh, Bill's to get some candy.

44:17.655 --> 44:20.647
You mean Phil's?
I'm sorry. Phil's. That's right.

44:20.724 --> 44:23.750
Frank, are you crazy?
Laura never lets him go out alone!

44:23.827 --> 44:25.692
Why not?
<i>[ Gunshots ]</i>

44:25.763 --> 44:27.458
[ Screams ]
<i>[ People Shouting ]</i>

44:27.531 --> 44:29.522
Oh, boy.

44:33.604 --> 44:37.438
<i>* [ Gospel: Woman Singing ]</i>

44:37.508 --> 44:40.602
<i>* [ Choir Singing ]</i>

44:48.519 --> 44:52.182
<i>* [ Woman Singing ]</i>

44:52.256 --> 44:55.123
<i>* [ Choir Singing ]</i>

